modules.description: Converts a three-argument function type into an S-expression by applying provided conversion functions for each argument. Works with polymorphic tuple types containing three distinct value types. Used to serialize complex function signatures in a structured, readable format for debugging or configuration.

Provides asynchronous versions of list and option operations, including map, filter, and bind, with support for concurrent execution. Works with lists, options, and promises, enabling non-blocking processing of sequential and conditional computations. Enables efficient handling of I/O-bound tasks such as parallel API calls or batched file reads.

Encapsulates asynchronous operations for event broadcasting and listening, enabling non-blocking communication between components. Supports custom serialization of three-argument functions into S-expressions using user-defined converters, facilitating debug logging and configuration export. Provides functions to register handlers, send events, and transform data structures for interoperability. Example uses include logging function calls with their arguments or persisting event schemas in a human-readable format.
